That's what i'm saying! Train guards are shaped like a wedge to dislodge anything away from the track. Have you seen one? Point being that unless the thing is attached to the track in a strong way, not like a latch that could break or fast and quick soldering, it will snap and be pushed to the side; thrown for long distances, more likely. trains usually go for 90-100 up to 130 km/h and they're very heavy. They will break anything like that. There was an article a long time ago about this sort of thing. That's why they have such strong and thick guards, not just for clearing snow and branches but for heavy logs or pieces of metal that might get stuck on the rail line.

>>894383884
The scale where you scan stuff is only for produce. When the self checkouts were first put in, the scale in the bagging area was a lot more sensitive, and there was a reasonably up to date database of the weight of lots of common items. Those first couple of months the scale will register if there is a weight difference. But over time with the actual inventory changing, and the changes in packaging, and just general wear and a lack of actual maintenance, those scales become horribly unreliable, to the point that most stores will disable or set them to only actually care about certain items.

All that said, theft is always wrong. Walmart bullies and exploits smaller businesses and suppliers, but they're big enough and profitable enough to absorb losses and pass them on elsewhere. You're not doing anything righteous by stealing from them, you're just giving them more incentive to low ball suppliers and underpay their workers.

Please know that I have grown and matured since my teenage years, and my musical tastes have broadened to include a wider range of artists and genres. I hope that we can find some common ground in the music that we enjoy together, and that we can create more positive memories as a family.

Thank you for your patience and understanding, and for always being there for me. I love you both very much, and I hope that you can forgive me for any pain that I may have caused you.

Sincerely,
Anon
